<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9800 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - DOOR WINDOW
        REGULATOR - MANUAL OR ELECTRIC
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>DOOR WINDOW REGULATOR - MANUAL OR ELECTRIC</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The cab door window regulator assembly
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601855">Item 3, Figure 55</hotlnk>) is serviced as a complete unit, manual or
                electric, left or right side. It is mounted on the aluminum plate (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601855">Item 1, Figure 55</hotlnk>) on the back side of the upper door trim panel (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601855">Item 2, Figure 55</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1601855" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1601855" filename="../figg16/G1601855.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 55. Cab Door Window Regulator Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. ALUMINUM PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. UPPER DOOR TRIM PANEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. WINDOW REGULATOR ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. VINYL TRIM MATERIAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. HEX NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. INNER DOOR HANDLE AND BRACKET</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove lower door trim panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601857">Item 4, Figure 57</hotlnk>). Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16018_13.xml" xrefid="hl1601802">HARDWARE AND TRIM, Remove
                        <xref refid="hl1601802"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">On passenger side door, remove trim panel screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601857">Item 2, Figure 57</hotlnk>) and remove lower door window trim (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601857">Item 3, Figure 57</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove upper door trim panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601857">Item 5, Figure 57</hotlnk>). Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16018_13.xml" xrefid="hl1601802">HARDWARE AND TRIM, Remove
                        <xref refid="hl1601802"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove 2 hex nuts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601855">Item 5, Figure 55</hotlnk>) and remove inner door handle and bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601855">Item 6, Figure 55</hotlnk>) from upper door trim panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601855">Item 2, Figure 55</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove 2 mounting screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601856">Item 1, Figure 56</hotlnk>) and remove ash tray (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601856">Item 2, Figure 56</hotlnk>) from upper door trim panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601856">Item 4, Figure 56</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1601856" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1601856" filename="../figg16/G1601856.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 56. Door Trim Panel</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. MOUNTING SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. ASH TRAY</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. VINYL TRIM PANEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. UPPER DOOR TRIM PANEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. WINDOW REGULATOR ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a putty knife and peel the vinyl trim material (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601855">Item 4, Figure 55</hotlnk>) from the right and left edges on back side of
                    upper door trim panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601855">Item 2, Figure 55</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise vinyl trim panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601856">Item 3, Figure 56</hotlnk>) on front side of upper door trim panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601856">Item 4, Figure 56</hotlnk>) up to access window regulator assembly
                    mounting screws.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove 4 screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601858">Figure 58</hotlnk>) retaining window regulator assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601855">Item 3, Figure 55</hotlnk>) to upper door trim panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601855">Item 2, Figure 55</hotlnk>). Remove window regulator assembly from back
                    side of upper door trim panel.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1601857" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1601857" filename="../figg16/G1601857.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 57. Passenger Side Door and Trim Panel</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. PASSENGER SIDE DOOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TRIM PANEL SCREWS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. LOWER DOOR WINDOW TRIM</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. LOWER DOOR TRIM PANEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. UPPER DOOR TRIM PANEL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1601858" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1601858" filename="../figg16/G1601858.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="152px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 58. Upper Door Trim Panel</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Lubricate window regulator gear teeth, arm pin and window guide at installation.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place window regulator assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601855">Item 3, Figure 55</hotlnk>) in position on back side of upper door trim
                    panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601855">Item 2, Figure 55</hotlnk>) and install 4 mounting screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601858">Figure 58</hotlnk>) on front side of upper door trim panel.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place vinyl trim covering in position on front side of upper door trim panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601855">Item 2, Figure 55</hotlnk>) and fold vinyl trim covering over and secure
                    right and left edges on back side.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install inner door handle and bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601855">Item 6, Figure 55</hotlnk>) on upper door trim panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601855">Item 2, Figure 55</hotlnk>) and secure with 2 hex nuts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601855">Item 5, Figure 55</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install ash tray (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601856">Item 2, Figure 56</hotlnk>) on upper door trim panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601856">Item 4, Figure 56</hotlnk>) and secure with 2 mounting screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601856">Item 1, Figure 56</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install upper door trim panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601857">Item 5, Figure 57</hotlnk>). Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16018_13.xml" xrefid="hl1601803">HARDWARE AND TRIM, Install
                        <xref refid="hl1601803"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Operate window to check window operation.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">On passenger side door, install lower door window trim (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601857">Item 3, Figure 57</hotlnk>) and install trim panel screws (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601857">Item 2, Figure 57</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install lower door trim panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601857">Item 4, Figure 57</hotlnk>). Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16018_13.xml" xrefid="hl1601803">HARDWARE AND TRIM, Install
                        <xref refid="hl1601803"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
